<subSubSection id="C31718D1CC194623CBB7FC06FE070680" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB24B5ACC194623CBB7FC06FE820558" blockId="25.[189,303,1329,1355]" box="[189,303,1329,1355]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<heading id="D0FAFC36CC194623CBB7FC06FE820558" bold="true" box="[189,303,1329,1355]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623CBB7FC06FE820558" bold="true" box="[189,303,1329,1355]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB24B5ACC194623CBB7FC68FE070680" blockId="25.[189,1399,1375,1683]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Synonymising 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623CA79FC68FD3E056A" authorityName="Ledoyer" authorityYear="1970" box="[371,659,1375,1401]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriellerythrops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbosa">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623CA79FC68FD3E056A" box="[371,659,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Siriellerythrops gibbosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
soon after its original description, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C36ABCC194623CF43FC57FABE0569" author="Bacescu M." box="[1097,1299,1375,1402]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="643 - 646" refId="ref37945" refString="Bacescu M. 1973 b. Contribution a la connaisance des mysides benthiques de la mer Rouge. Rapports et Proces-Verbaux des Reunions (International Commission for the Scientific Exploration of the Mediterranean Sea) 21 (9): 643 - 646." type="journal article" year="1973">
Băcescu (
<date id="FFB36D9ACC194623CFB5FC68FB560569" box="[1215,1275,1375,1402]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1973">1973</date>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
did not provide any comments about his comparisons and decision. The original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C36ABCC194623CFCEFCB5FAC3058E" author="Ledoyer M." box="[1220,1390,1410,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="223 - 227" refId="ref38659" refString="Ledoyer M. 1970. Mysidaces des herbiers de phanerogames marines de Tulear (Madagascar). Etude systematique et ecologique. Recueil des Travaux de la Station Marine d'Endoume 10: 223 - 227." type="journal article" year="1970">
Ledoyer 
<date id="FFB36D9ACC194623CE38FCB4FAC3058E" box="[1330,1390,1411,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1970">1970</date>
</bibRefCitation>
) and illustrations of this species were detailed; comparing them with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623C8F4FC91FB1505D3" authorityName="Paulson" authorityYear="1875" box="[1022,1208,1446,1472]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudata">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623C8F4FC91FB1505D3" box="[1022,1208,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. brevicaudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one can easily find multiple differences between the two species, particularly in the shape of the anterodorsal margin of the carapace, shape and armature of the telson, setation of maxilla 2, armature of uropodal endopods and eye shape. Supporting the opinion of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C36ABCC194623C9B1FF27FBAE063A" author="Murano M. &amp; Fukuoka K." box="[699,1027,1551,1578]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref38907" refString="Murano M. &amp; Fukuoka K. 2008. A systematic study of the genus Siriella (Crustacea: Mysida) from the Pacific and Indian Oceans, with descriptions of fifteen new species. National Museum of Nature and Science Monographs 36: 1 - 173." type="journal article" year="2008">
Murano &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49C985B8CC194623C84EFF38FC06063A" box="[836,939,1551,1577]" country="Japan" name="Fukuoka" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fukuoka</collectingRegion>
(
<date id="FFB36D9ACC194623C8B7FF38FC56063A" box="[957,1019,1551,1577]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2008">2008</date>
)
</bibRefCitation>
about significant difference of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623CBB7FF04FE97065F" authorityName="Ledoyer" authorityYear="1970" box="[189,314,1586,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriellerythrops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbosa">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623CBB7FF04FE97065F" box="[189,314,1586,1613]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. gibbosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623CA8DFF04FDEC065F" authorityName="Paulson" authorityYear="1875" box="[391,577,1586,1613]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudata">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623CA8DFF04FDEC065F" box="[391,577,1586,1613]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. brevicaudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we re-establish the species here. At the same time, we synonymise the genus name 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623CA74FF61FD440663" authority="Ledoyer, 1970" authorityName="Ledoyer" authorityYear="1970" box="[382,745,1622,1648]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriellerythrops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623CA74FF61FD980663" box="[382,565,1622,1648]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Siriellerythrops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C36ABCC194623C934FF61FD440663" author="Ledoyer M." box="[574,745,1622,1648]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="223 - 227" refId="ref38659" refString="Ledoyer M. 1970. Mysidaces des herbiers de phanerogames marines de Tulear (Madagascar). Etude systematique et ecologique. Recueil des Travaux de la Station Marine d'Endoume 10: 223 - 227." type="journal article" year="1970">Ledoyer, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623C824FF61FBBB0663" authority="Dana, 1850" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1850" box="[814,1046,1621,1648]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623C824FF61FC290663" box="[814,900,1622,1648]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Siriella</emphasis>
Dana, 1850
</taxonomicName>
and include 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623CFA5FF61FA860663" authorityName="Ledoyer" authorityYear="1970" box="[1199,1323,1622,1648]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriellerythrops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbosa">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623CFA5FF61FA860663" box="[1199,1323,1622,1648]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">S. gibbosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D30D9CC194623CBB7FF4EFEFA0680" authorityName="Paulson" authorityYear="1875" box="[189,343,1657,1683]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Siriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudata">
<emphasis id="B9799748CC194623CBB7FF4EFEFA0680" box="[189,343,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">brevicaudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
